  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX trading at 6591 right at the GEX flip strike and dealers in a PIN regime, they're currently neutral but poised to provide stabilizing flow - selling any push toward the massive +91.6B gamma wall at 6600 and buying any dip toward 6575 negative gamma. The 27.9% GEX surge and wall break detection suggests recent volatility has dealers repositioning, but the overwhelming positive gamma structure above (6595-6610 strikes all showing 30B+ walls) creates a strong ceiling that will trigger aggressive dealer selling on rallies. Key levels to watch are immediate resistance at 6595 (+41.5B) and the critical 6600 strike where maximum dealer selling pressure awaits.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect the market to get pinned below 6600 with dealers capping upside moves.",
